Build-Depends: debhelper (>= 7.0.50~), linux-headers-generic, libgtk2.0-dev, libwrap0-dev, libjpeg62-dev, libmagickwand-dev, doxygen, swig, texlive-latex-base, ghostscript
Standards-Version: 3.9.0
Homepage: http://carmen.sourceforge.net/

Package: carmen
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Recommends: carmen-data
Suggests: carmen-doc
Description: The Carnegie Mellon Robot Navigation Toolkit
 CARMEN is an open-source collection of software for mobile robot control.
 It is modular software designed to provide basic navigation primatives
 including: base and sensor control, logging, obstacle avoidance,
 localization, path planning, and mapping.

